                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>The hand seems to be the same as that of
                        Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel manuscripts of May ʾAbʾa Māryām (BQM-009) and Golʿa Yoḥannǝs
                        (BGY-013), cp. also AMM-007.<date>Second half of 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; headings of the Gospels; the word
                           mǝʿrāf, chapter numbers and the signs between them; usually, two lines on
                           the incipit of each chapter; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 Incipit of Text I and of its subsections; incipits of Text
                           II, III, IV; incipits of the Evangelists' biographies; on the incipit
                           pages of Text I, II, III, IV, IV, a few lines are rubricated (in groups
                           of two lines, alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
